<br>
<br>
Sell:LSoEE, Goblin Skull Earring(only used as crap buff), <br>
Chest:Engraved Velium Fieldplate<br>
Shoulders:Crested Spauldors<br>
Face:Crystal Spider Eyes<br>
Earrings:Vahshir Claw, Earring of the Solstice, if you can't afford solstice, get Griffon Fang(?).<br>
Neck:Clattering Bone Necklace<br>
Waist:Sash of the Dragonborn or SBoC<br>
Gauntlets:Cobalt or MQ Champions<br>
Wrists:Silver Chitin Wristbands<br>
Legs:Crusty Greaves<br>
Offhand:Frostbringer<br>
Helm:Radulkan<br>
Back:Cloak of the Maelstrom<br>
Iventory:Grobb Liquidised Meat,Halas Meat pies(seriously)<br>
<br>
Need to keep something in mind.. warriors aren't damage dealers. It doesn't matter if you don't do as much damage when you ditch your LSoEE, the FB proc is what you need, AGGRO. Your job is to keep aggro and take the damage and nothing else. <br>
<br>
Heck, I'd wield a 1/30 weapon with enraging blow on it just because it would do my job.<br>
<br>
Also, keep in mind you don't die when you run out of dex, you die when you run out of HP. I have moderately ok gear that puts me at 3500hp/1200ac/132dex, and I do just fine. But that's because I have solid gear.<br>
<br>
Against what you'll be competing to hold aggro against for your level, 1 FB proc will give you aggro the entire fight.<br>
<br>
<br>
Main focus:STA/HP/AC/Aggro, everything else=trash<br>
